    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>Feby 12/66</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. I Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir and Friend,</p>
            <p>I wished to see you when I was<lb/> at home on <date>Sunday</date> last, but had<lb/>
                not the opportunity to do so.<lb/> As my preceptor and very old friend, I<lb/> deem
                it my duty and at the same<lb/> time a pleasure to inform you of<lb/> my engagement
                to <persName>miss Julia Spanier</persName><lb/> formerly of
                    <placeName>Albany</placeName>, but now of this<lb/> city — I think you are
                well<lb/> acquainted with the family, and I trust<lb/> to have the pleasure ere long
                of introducing<lb/> you to the young lady I drop you<lb/> these few lines, as I know
                they they will<lb/> give you pleasure, and am as always,</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Your very true friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">M. M. Allen</persName>,</p>
            <p>(Over)</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>P. S. I received this last week<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">credentials</hi> for the orthodox <add>אמונת אבותינו</add><lb/>
                <add>קהלה</add> of <placeName>Fort Wayne</placeName>, to represent<lb/> them in the
                “Board of American Israelites”<lb/>
                <persName role="author">M.</persName></p>
        </body>
    </text>
